.TH Sherpa 1 22.11.2008 Sherpa ""
.SH NAME
Sherpa \- Monte Carlo event generator
.SH SYNOPSIS
Sherpa
.B "[\-gbvh] [\-f \fIfile\fP] [\-p \fIpath\fP] "
.br
.B "       [\-O \fIlevel\fP] [\-j \fIthreads\fP]"
.br
.B "       [\-e \fIevents\fP] [\-a \fIanalyses\fP] [\-A \fIpath\fP]"
.br
.B "       [\-m \fIgenerators\fP] [\-w \fImode\fP] [\-r \fIresults\fP]"
.br
.B "       [\-s \fIshower\fP] [\-F \fImodule\fP] [\-D \fImodule\fP]"
.br
.B "       [\-L \fIpath\fP] [\-R \fIseed\fP] [\-l \fIlogfile\fP]"
.br
.B "       [\fIPARAMETER1=VALUE1\fP [\fIPARAMETER2=VALUE2\fP ... ] ]"
.br
.B "       [\fITAG1:=VALUE1\fP [\fITAG2:=VALUE2\fP ... ] ]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
Sherpa is a Monte Carlo event generation framework.
.br
This manual page contains only the very basic information on the
synopsis of Sherpa. The full description is maintained as a TeXinfo manual.
.SH OPTIONS
.IP "\fB-f\fP \fIfile\fP" 
Sets the runcard name to \fIfile\fP. 
.IP "\fB-p\fP \fIpath\fP"
Sets the run path name to \fIpath\fP.
.IP "\fB-e\fP \fIevents\fP"
Sets the number of events to \fIevents\fP.
.IP "\fB-r\fP \fIresults\fP"
Sets the result directory name to \fIresults\fP.
.IP "\fB-m\fP \fIgenerators\fP"
Sets the ME generator list to \fIgenerators\fP.
.IP "\fB-w\fP \fImode\fP"
Sets the event generation mode to \fImode\fP.
.IP "\fB-s\fP \fIshower\fP"
Sets the parton shower generator \fIshower\fP.
.IP "\fB-F\fP \fImodule\fP"
Sets the fragmentation module \fImodule\fP.
.IP "\fB-D\fP \fImodule\fP"
Sets the decay module \fImodule\fP.
.IP "\fB-L\fP \fIpath\fP"
Sets the process library path to \fIpath\fP.
.IP "\fB-R\fP \fIseed\fP"
Sets the random seed to \fIseed\fP.
.IP "\fB-l\fP \fIlogfile\fP"
Sets the log file name to \fIlogfile\fP.
.IP "\fB-a\fP \fIanalyses\fP"
Sets the analysis handler list to \fIanalyses\fP.
.IP "\fB-A\fP \fIpath\fP"
Sets the analysis output path \fIpath\fP.
.IP "\fB-O\fP \fIlevel\fP"
Sets the output level \fIlevel\fP.
.IP "\fB-o\fP \fIlevel\fP"
Sets the event output level \fIlevel\fP.
.IP "\fB-j\fP \fIthreads\fP"
Sets the number of threads \fIthreads\fP.
.IP "\fB-g\fP"
Does not create the result directory.
.IP "\fB-b\fP"
Switches to non-batch mode.
.IP "\fB-v\fP, \fB--version\fP" 
Prints versioning information.
.IP "\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP" 
Prints a short help message.
.IP "\fBPARAMETER\fP=\fIVALUE\fP" 
Sets the value of a parameter\fP. 
.br
.IP "\fBTAG:\fP=\fIVALUE\fP" 
Sets the value of a tag\fP. 
.SH EXAMPLE
This is an example for the first invocation of Sherpa

.RS 2
.B Sherpa -p LHC/ -f Run.dat
.RE
.RE

The program uses run parameter specifications listed in the 
base file \fIRun.dat\fP residing in the directory \fILHC\fP.
.SH FILES
Example files are found in the \fBshare\fP directory.
